at Risk to recognize that

00:38:24.570 --> 00:38:30.790
portfolios can sometimes co-vary
more than we thought.

00:38:30.790 --> 00:38:33.810
That there might be episodes
when everything goes wrong at

00:38:33.810 --> 00:38:34.820
the same time.

00:38:34.820 --> 00:38:39.600
So, suddenly the covariance
goes up.

00:38:39.600 --> 00:38:46.160
So, CoVaR is an alternative
to Value at Risk that does

00:38:46.160 --> 00:38:49.120
different kinds of
calculations.

